# Certificate Authenticity Verification System — Implementation Plan

Build a full-stack web application that automatically detects tampered or edited certificates by comparing uploaded certificate data with official verification sources.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — Python Flask API

#### [NEW] [requirements.txt](file:///N:/Verify/backend/requirements.txt)
Dependencies: `flask`, `flask-cors`, `pytesseract`, `PyMuPDF (fitz)`, `Pillow`, `opencv-python`, `pyzbar`, `beautifulsoup4`, `requests`, `playwright`, `python-dotenv`, `werkzeug`

---

#### [NEW] [app.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/app.py)
Flask application entry point:
- Configure CORS, upload folder, and max file size (16 MB)
- Register API blueprint
- Serve uploaded files

#### [NEW] [routes.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/routes.py)
API routes:
- `POST /api/verify` — accepts PDF/image upload, runs full pipeline, returns JSON result
- `GET /api/history` — returns in-memory verification history
- `GET /api/history/<id>` — returns a single past result

---

#### [NEW] [extractor.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/extractor.py)
Text extraction module:
- `extract_text_from_pdf(path)` — uses PyMuPDF to get embedded text; falls back to OCR
- `extract_text_from_image(path)` — uses Tesseract OCR via `pytesseract`
- `extract_fields(text)` — regex + heuristic parsing to pull **name, course, institution, date, certificate ID, verification URL**

#### [NEW] [qr_detector.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/qr_detector.py)
QR code module:
- `detect_qr(image_path)` — uses `pyzbar` + OpenCV to find and decode QR codes
- Returns list of decoded URLs

#### [NEW] [scraper.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/scraper.py)
Web scraping module:
- `fetch_official_data(url)` — uses `requests` + BeautifulSoup for static pages
- Falls back to Playwright for JS-rendered pages
- Extracts official name, course, institution, date, certificate ID from verification page
- Platform-specific parsers for Coursera, Udemy, edX, LinkedIn Learning

#### [NEW] [comparator.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/comparator.py)
Comparison engine:
- `compare_fields(uploaded, official)` — field-by-field comparison (name, course, institution, date, ID)
- Uses fuzzy string matching (`difflib.SequenceMatcher`) to handle minor OCR inaccuracies
- Returns per-field match/mismatch details + overall authenticity score (0–100%)

#### [NEW] [tampering.py](file:///N:/Verify/backend/tampering.py)
Image tampering detection:
- `analyze_tampering(image_path)` — runs multiple checks:
  - **ELA (Error Level Analysis)** — resave at known quality, amplify difference to reveal edits
  - **Metadata analysis** — check for Photoshop/editor signatures in EXIF
  - **Font consistency** — basic variance check across text regions
- Returns tampering indicators with confidence levels

---

### Frontend — React + Vite

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/package.json)
Vite React project with dependencies: `react-dropzone`, `framer-motion`, `lucide-react`, `axios`

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/index.html)
HTML shell with Google Fonts (Inter) and meta tags

#### [NEW] [src/main.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/main.jsx)
React entry point, renders `<App />`

#### [NEW] [src/App.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/App.jsx)
Root component with client-side routing (hash-based):
- `/` → Upload page
- `/result` → Results dashboard
- `/history` → Verification history

#### [NEW] [src/index.css](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/index.css)
Design system:
- CSS variables for colors, gradients, shadows, typography
- Dark theme by default with light mode toggle
- Glassmorphism card styles, animated gradients, smooth transitions

#### [NEW] [src/components/Header.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/components/Header.jsx)
Fixed top bar with logo, navigation, and dark/light toggle

#### [NEW] [src/components/UploadZone.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/components/UploadZone.jsx)
Drag-and-drop upload area (using `react-dropzone`):
- Accepts PDF, JPG, PNG
- File preview, size validation
- Animated border on hover/drag

#### [NEW] [src/components/ProgressTracker.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/components/ProgressTracker.jsx)
Step-by-step progress indicator:
- Steps: Upload → Text Extraction → URL Detection → Fetching Official Data → Comparison → Result
- Animated transitions between steps, checkmarks on completion

#### [NEW] [src/components/ResultDashboard.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/components/ResultDashboard.jsx)
Main results view:
- Authenticity score gauge (animated circular progress)
- Status badge (Verified / Tampered / Unverifiable)
- Field-by-field comparison table with color-coded match/mismatch
- Tampering analysis indicators
- Downloadable report (JSON summary)

#### [NEW] [src/components/HistoryList.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/components/HistoryList.jsx)
Verification history table with timestamp, filename, score, and status

#### [NEW] [src/components/ScoreGauge.jsx](file:///N:/Verify/frontend/src/components/ScoreGauge.jsx)
Animated SVG circular gauge for the authenticity score (0–100%)

