## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tesseract OCR** must be installed on your system for OCR to work. On Windows: download the installer from [UB Mannheim](https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki). The backend will look for it at the default install path.

> [!WARNING]
> **Web scraping of real verification pages** (Coursera, Udemy, etc.) depends on those sites' current HTML structure. Scrapers may break if sites change. For the demo, we will include mock/simulated verification data so the project works end-to-end without external dependencies.

> [!NOTE]
> **Playwright** requires a one-time browser install command: `playwright install chromium`. This is only needed if scraping JS-heavy verification pages.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. **Backend unit test** — `python -m pytest backend/tests/` covering:
   - Text extraction from a sample PDF and image
   - URL regex extraction
   - Field comparison logic and scoring
   - QR detection on a test image
2. **Frontend build** — `cd N:\Verify\frontend && npm run build` to confirm no build errors

### Browser Verification
1. Start backend: `cd N:\Verify\backend && python app.py`
2. Start frontend: `cd N:\Verify\frontend && npm run dev`
3. Open the app in the browser
4. Upload a sample certificate (we will include a test PDF)
5. Verify the progress tracker animates through each step
6. Confirm the results dashboard shows the authenticity score, field comparison, and tampering indicators
7. Check the history page records the verification
